<h1 id="list-all-sites">Sites</h1>

<h2>List all sites</h2>

<p>
  By default, this endpoint retrieves all the sites.
  <br>
  Sites can be filtered by name, address, zip code or city.
</p>

<p>
  Things to consider:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    Sites are <strong>sorted</strong> by alphabetical order based on their name.
  </li>
  <li>
    There is <strong>no pagination</strong>.
  </li>
</ul>

<h3>Endpoint</h3>

<code>GET /v2/sites</code>

<h3>Parameters</h3>

<p>Use them to filter out the results.</p>

<table class="u-full-width">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Filter</th>
      <th>Optional</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><code>search</code></td>
      <td>true</td>
      <td>
        When provided, it returns only the sites which name, address, zip code
        or city contains the given value.
        <br>
        Note that it is <strong>case insensitive</strong>.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Request example</h3>

<code>curl "/v2/sites"</code>

